column3: >Medallion Signature Guarantees - The Operating Agreement with Charles Schwab, dated March 28, 1996,

column1: Fund Company agrees to transfer shares between accounts for Schwab customers or other street name brokers held directly with a Fund and the Account on the Fund's records.
column2: For the purpose of expediting direct transfers from accounts for Schwab customers, Fund Company will accept by facsimile transmission a summary sheet of information indicating the customers' names, account numbers, the Fund affected and the number of shares to be re-registered.&#160
column3: For record keeping purposes, actual copies of transfer forms will be forwarded to a Fund on a weekly basis, upon the Fund's request for such forms.&#160
column4: Schwab represents and warrants that for each transfer indicated in the summary sheet of information, it holds each underlying instruction for re-registration signed by its customer, and that its customer's signature on such instruction is signature guaranteed by Schwab pursuant to the New York Stock Exchange's Medallion Signature Program.

column3: >Invoicing - The Schwab invoice breaks out RPS assets only for funds that are subject to different fee rates for RPS and non-RPS assets.
column4: For funds subject to the same fee rate for RPS and non-RPS assets, the invoice and data warehouse show all assets as non-RPS.

column1: Schwab invoices 12b-1 and Sub TA fees as one combined rate (e.g. 35 bp for a 25 bp 12b-1 fee and 10 bp Sub TA fee).​

column3: >Minimum Fee - Note that the Schwab agreement offers a 6 month introductory waiver period for each new fund subject to the minimum fee.
column4: No minimum fee will be billed for the first 6 months a fund is available.

column1: Only where this Agreement is duly executed by each party and such parties are not in breach of any other agreement among the parties and each condition noted below is met will such transfers be processed without providing individual customer authorization.
<div><em>Requirements for transfers that qualify for this special transfer procedure&#58
1. All supporting documentation, i.e. original customer authorization, will be furnished upon request to HCA Securities, Inc.*, Harbor Transfer, Inc.* or Harbor Fund*.
2. Firm requesting the transfer, must be the firm that was broker/dealer of record for the account at the time of transaction and/or was the firm that initiated the transfer.
3. All requests for such transfers will be presented on Pershing firm letterhead.
4. All requests will be submitted either via fax, federal express, or e-mail and will contain Pershing's official signature guarantee and standard indemnification clause.
HCA Securities, Inc.* and Harbor Transfer, Inc.*, under this Letter of Indemnification Agreement, hereby agree to process transfers requested by Pershing on behalf of their customer.
